The method should return an integer value representing the number of vowel substrings in the input string `word`.
The method should not modify the input string `word`.
The method should handle both uppercase and lowercase vowels.
The method should consider a substring as a vowel substring if it contains one or more vowels.
The method should count overlapping vowel substrings separately. For example, if the input string is "aa", the method should count it as two vowel substrings.
The method should return 0 if there are no vowel substrings in the input string `word`.
